Lectura de la base de datos

require(geoR)
## Loading required package: geoR
## Loading required package: sp
## Loading required package: MASS
## --------------------------------------------------------------
##  Analysis of geostatistical data
##  For an Introduction to geoR go to http://www.leg.ufpr.br/geoR
##  geoR version 1.7-4.1 (built on 2012-06-29) is now loaded
## --------------------------------------------------------------
elevation<-read.geodata("elevation2.txt",header=T)
points(elevation,cex.min=1,cex.max=4)

Histograma de frecuencia de la variable objetivo

hist(elevation$data,xlab="Elevación",ylab="Frecuencia",
     main="Histograma de elevación")

Perfil con en dirección W-E

with(elevation, plot(coords[, 1], data, xlab = "W-E",
   ylab = "datos de elevación", pch = 19, cex = 1))
lines(lowess(elevation$data ~ elevation$coords[, 1]))

Perfil con en dirección S-N

with(elevation, plot(coords[, 2], data, xlab = "S-N",
  ylab = "datos de elevación", pch = 19, cex = 1))
lines(with(elevation, lowess(data ~ coords[, 2])))

Diagrama de dispersión de puntos e identificación de residuales

Datos originales

points(elevation, cex.min=1, cex.max = 4)

Quitando la tendencia lineal

points(elevation, trend = "1st", pt.div = 2, abs.residuals = T,  cex.var=elevation$data,
        cex.max = 4)

Quitando la tendencia cuadrática

points(elevation, trend = "2nd", pt.div = 2, abs.residuals= T,cex.var=elevation$data,
        cex.max = 4)

Semivariogramas empíricos

Semivariograma de los datos originales

plot(variog(elevation, uvec = seq(0, 50, by = 5)), type = "b",xlab="Distancia",ylab="Semivarianza")
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram

Semivariogramas quitando la tendencia lineal y la cuadrática

res1.v <- variog(elevation, trend = "1st", uvec = seq(0, 50, by = 5))
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(res1.v, type = "b",xlab="Distancia",ylab="Semivarianza")

res2.v <- variog(elevation, trend = "2nd", uvec = seq(0,50, by = 5))
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
lines(res2.v, type = "b", lty = 2)

Prueba de estructura espacial mediante simulación

Sin la tendencia lineal

set.seed(231)
mc1 <- variog.mc.env(elevation, obj = res1.v)
## variog.env: generating 99 simulations by permutating data values
## variog.env: computing the empirical variogram for the 99 simulations
## variog.env: computing the envelops
plot(res1.v, env = mc1, xlab="Distancia",ylab="Semivarianza")

Sin la tendencia lineal

set.seed(231)
mc2 <- variog.mc.env(elevation, obj = res2.v)
## variog.env: generating 99 simulations by permutating data values
## variog.env: computing the empirical variogram for the 99 simulations
## variog.env: computing the envelops
plot(res2.v, env = mc2, xlab="Distancia",ylab="Semivarianza")
